The Nigeria Sovereign Investment Authority (NSIA), in partnership with the Presidential Infrastructure Development Fund (PIDF), has donated patrol vehicles to the Nigeria Police Force (NPF). The handover ceremony held on Tuesday at the force headquarters in Abuja. According to the NSIA, 16 Innoson pickup trucks (IVM carrier) were donated to the police as part of efforts to improve surveillance on the Abuja-Kaduna-Kano road. Usman Baba, the inspector-general of police, and Uche Orji, managing director and chief executive officer of NSIA, were in attendance. NSIA serves as the fund manager to the Presidential Infrastructure Development Fund (PIDF). One of the projects under the PIDF is the Abuja-Kano-Kaduna road project, which stretches from Abuja to Kano through Zaria and Kaduna. Below are photos. <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-681022" src="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/FPChoJYXsAskx2b.jpeg" alt="" width="1080" height="720" srcset="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/FPChoJYXsAskx2b.jpeg 1080w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/FPChoJYXsAskx2b-300x200.jpeg 300w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/FPChoJYXsAskx2b-1024x683.jpeg 1024w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/FPChoJYXsAskx2b-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/FPChoJYXsAskx2b-24x16.jpeg 24w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/FPChoJYXsAskx2b-36x24.jpeg 36w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/FPChoJYXsAskx2b-48x32.jpeg 48w" sizes="(max-width: 1080px) 100vw, 1080px" /> <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-681023" src="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/FPChn3JXIA4EvSg.jpeg" alt="" width="1080" height="720" srcset="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/FPChn3JXIA4EvSg.jpeg 1080w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content